    <div class="content-subhead">
        <h2><a href="https://github.com/proverbialsunrise/hymnalapp">hymnalApp</a></h2>
    </div> 

    <p>
        In 2010 (fresh off my first work term at Apple) I decided I wanted to build an app for viewing hymns for phones.  I got together with a friend, and we built a cross-platform (iOS and Android) application for searching for and viewing hymns from the Mennonite Hymnal.  Unfortunately, we were unable to secure the electronic rights for distribution of the hymn files as the publisher of the Hymnal did not own these rights.  The app contained a cross-platform datalayer built in C++ that was used by both the Android (through the JNI) and iOS (using Objective C++) versions while the UI code for each application was built in the native languages (Java and Objective-C).  
    </p>
    
    
